The tracker at misato has been down for a while.  This is because we've
discovered a problem with Java and 'dyndns' host names.  The problem is
that once Java looks up a host name, it caches the IP address
indefinately.  There is no way to flush this cache or force a fresh
lookup.  So, if you change the IP address for your dyndns host name,
the tracker will never be able to find your NPDS server again, because it
will be trying to contact the old IP address.

The (apparent) fix for this is either to wait until Java 1.4, or set a
parameter in Java 1.2 or later to control the amount of time that Java
caches the IP addresses.  Unfortunately, when I turned this option on it
started triggering server checks every minute.  I shut it off and haven't
had time to look at it yet.

