I get these occasionally after someone takes a bunch of screenshots one 
after another. I think it has something to do with a certain part of a 
connection not getting closed correctly. I could be way off though. Just 
a though... if you are using port 80 to serve through, and you server is 
accessible publicly, you might want to try a different port (like 8080 or 
similar). Every once in a while, when the Code Red and other assorted 
Microsnot-targeted viruses start propagating, they can hammer web servers 
that use the default port 80 pretty hard. Since I've started using an 
alternate port, NPDS has been much more stable.

